<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911104-0147</DOCNO><DOCID>911104-0147.</DOCID><HL>   Laserscope Sets Rights Plan</HL><DATE>11/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LSCP</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>DIVIDENDS (DIV)MEDICAL andamp; BIOTECHNOLOGY, GENETIC RESEARCH, PROSTHETICS (MTC)</IN><NS>DIVIDENDS (DIV)SHAREHOLDER RIGHTS PLANS (SRP)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Laserscope, a maker of surgical lasersystems, said its directors declared a dividend distributionof one common share purchase right on each common shareoutstanding.   The rights, exercisable at $34 a share, would go intoeffect after a person or group begins an offer for 20% ormore of Laserscope stock.</LP><TEXT>   The company said the rights plan is designed to ensurethat its shareholders receive fair treatment in the event ofan attempted takeover.</TEXT></DOC>